- Use bootable flash to go into repair > troubleshooting > command prompt
- manage-bde -status
- manage-bde -unlock C: -RecoveryPassword <your_recovery_key_here>
- if drive C not labeled
- diskpart
- list volume
- select volume (os volume ussually the largest
- assign letter=E (any letter)
- exit
- manage-bde -unlock C: -RecoveryPassword <your_recovery_key_here>
- temporaly disable bitlocker ( manage-bde -protectors -disable C:)
- exit and restart
- enable bitlocker once logged in
  manage-bde -protectors -enable C:
  or via GUI
